   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The Document panel allows you to view all clauses and fields in your agreement document
            which can be edited. These clauses and fields are marked as <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">smart clauses </b>and
                <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">smart fields</b> in the document template from which the document was generated. </p>
      <note type="note" class="- topic/note ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Unless explicitly stated, any mention in this guide of fields or
                clauses should be considered a reference to smart fields and clauses.</p>
      </note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To use the Document Panel, hover over the <image placement="inline"
                width="20"
                href="../attachments/45220125/49676341.png"
                id="image_xhb_lpn_12c"
                class="- topic/image "/>
         <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Document</b> icon
         in the X-Author pane to display two menu choices: <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Fields</b> and <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clauses</b>.</p>
      <fig id="fig_btn_mpn_12c" class="- topic/fig ">
         <image height="250"
                placement="break"
                width="277"
                href="../attachments/45220125/49676342.png"
                id="image_ctn_mpn_12c"
                class="- topic/image "/>
      </fig>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Based on your selection, the Document panel shows either the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Fields </b>or
                <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clauses</b> view. You can use the Document Panel to:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">View changed fields and clauses.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Modify field values.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Reject changes to clause content.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Reject changes to field values.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Validate values of changed fields.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Mark clauses for deletion or undelete a clause.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Unmark marked clauses.</li>
      </ul>
